## When to use
When you need detailed information about the performance and load of individual CPU cores in a Linux system.

## Approach
Use the `shell_exec` tool with the `mpstat` command. Common options include `-P ALL` for monitoring all processors, `-I 1` to sample data every second, and `-o CSV` for outputting results in CSV format which can be easily parsed and analyzed.

## Example
```sh
shell_exec "mpstat -P ALL -I 1 -o CSV"
```
This example uses the `shell_exec` tool to run an mpstat command that monitors CPU usage by each processor core every second, providing detailed statistics in a CSV format.

## Pitfalls
- Ensure that the system has installed and configured the `mpstat` utility.
- Be aware of the sampling interval which can affect the accuracy and detail of the results.